1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:12,000
(Watch on www.kisskh.li Support Admin)

2
00:00:14,120 --> 00:00:17,020
(Yoo Yeon Seok)

3
00:00:17,120 --> 00:00:20,160
(Esom)

4
00:00:20,660 --> 00:00:24,900
(Kim Kyung Nam)

5
00:00:24,960 --> 00:00:28,900
(Kim Mi Kyung, Jeon Seok Ho, Son Yeo Eun, Lee Ah Rin)

6
00:00:29,600 --> 00:00:33,270
(Choi Kwang Il, Jung Seung Gil, Yeon Je Hyung)

7
00:00:44,080 --> 00:00:47,990
(Phantom Lawyer)

8
00:00:48,020 --> 00:00:49,920
(Supported by Ministry of Culture, Sports and KOCCA)

9
00:00:49,990 --> 00:00:51,489
(All people, places, and events in this drama are fictional.)

10
00:00:51,490 --> 00:00:52,920
(Child actors filmed safely with guardians.)

11
00:00:52,990 --> 00:00:54,089
(All scenes involving animals were staged...)

12
00:00:54,090 --> 00:00:55,260
(and filmed safely by welfare standards.)

13
00:00:56,160 --> 00:00:57,360
Sir.

14
00:00:58,600 --> 00:00:59,600
Yes?

15
00:01:02,030 --> 00:01:03,130
Hey.

16
00:01:03,640 --> 00:01:04,840
Are you okay?

17
00:01:05,300 --> 00:01:07,370
Who are you?

18
00:01:08,770 --> 00:01:09,770
What?

19
00:01:10,480 --> 00:01:11,510
I mean...

20
00:01:12,840 --> 00:01:13,950
Where am I?

21
00:01:25,660 --> 00:01:26,660
What's wrong?

22
00:01:27,190 --> 00:01:29,390
He's reset again.

23
00:01:33,630 --> 00:01:37,540
Our client is gone, and the will has been forged.

24
00:01:37,970 --> 00:01:40,170
So we have no grounds to continue this trial.

25
00:01:41,410 --> 00:01:45,710
Still, let's not give up. Let's wait until she gets here.

26
00:01:46,480 --> 00:01:47,580
I'm sorry.

27
00:01:49,750 --> 00:01:50,750
Ma'am.

28
00:01:51,950 --> 00:01:53,180
Ma'am, are you okay?

29
00:01:57,920 --> 00:02:00,330
- Here, have a seat. - Thank you.

30
00:02:10,640 --> 00:02:11,870
I apologize.

31
00:02:13,810 --> 00:02:15,140
About the will...

32
00:02:16,210 --> 00:02:18,210
Did you really dictate them, ma'am?

33
00:02:19,640 --> 00:02:20,750
Yes, I did.

34
00:02:21,910 --> 00:02:23,350
I dictated it,

35
00:02:24,420 --> 00:02:26,020
and my husband wrote it down.

36
00:02:26,720 --> 00:02:27,720
Ma'am.

37
00:02:29,590 --> 00:02:31,620
Why did you file a complaint against Ryeo Seon Hwa?

38
00:02:33,190 --> 00:02:35,430
You said you two were like family.

39
00:02:49,640 --> 00:02:51,480
From the moment I first saw him,

40
00:02:52,180 --> 00:02:54,110
I fell for him.

41
00:02:54,680 --> 00:02:56,480
(Ideal Shoes)

42
00:03:02,420 --> 00:03:03,790
But after getting to know him,

43
00:03:04,490 --> 00:03:08,629
he was far more wonderful than I ever imagined.

44
00:03:08,630 --> 00:03:11,100
- Are you all right? - Yes, I'm fine. Thank you.

45
00:03:14,100 --> 00:03:16,700
And so, my feelings for him grew stronger.

46
00:03:17,670 --> 00:03:19,570
- Come what may, - You're not hurt, are you?

47
00:03:19,900 --> 00:03:22,470
- No, I'm not hurt. - I decided to confess my feelings.

48
00:03:22,940 --> 00:03:24,010
All right, take care now.

49
00:03:24,410 --> 00:03:25,610
But then...

50
00:03:26,680 --> 00:03:27,880
He was...

51
00:03:28,780 --> 00:03:31,480
making a pair of red shoes.

52
00:03:35,150 --> 00:03:37,290
I thought the shoes were for me,

53
00:03:37,920 --> 00:03:39,660
and I can't tell you how excited I was.

54
00:03:40,730 --> 00:03:41,930
Are they ready?

55
00:03:42,430 --> 00:03:47,300
- Yes. They're almost done. - But I was wrong.

56
00:03:47,530 --> 00:03:48,830
They're absolutely beautiful.

57
00:03:49,170 --> 00:03:51,070
- And right there... - Pretty, aren't they?

58
00:03:51,340 --> 00:03:53,000
was Seon Hwa.

59
00:03:55,370 --> 00:03:58,040
I was so angry, and I went straight to a bar.

60
00:03:59,710 --> 00:04:02,250
There's this man I like.

61
00:04:05,220 --> 00:04:07,650
But he's in love with another woman.

62
00:04:09,520 --> 00:04:11,660
I don't get what he sees in a woman who has a kid in the North.

63
00:04:12,520 --> 00:04:13,660
- Seon Hwa! - Jeong Hee.

64
00:04:13,760 --> 00:04:15,060
And then, a few days later,

65
00:04:15,760 --> 00:04:18,400
- they took Seon Hwa away. - Put her in.

66
00:04:19,560 --> 00:04:21,730
The North? You mean North Korea?

67
00:04:22,530 --> 00:04:24,370
- It was him. - Seon Hwa!

68
00:04:24,640 --> 00:04:26,470
- Sir. - Seon Hwa!

69
00:04:27,810 --> 00:04:30,740
From that moment on, I wasn't myself.

70
00:04:31,980 --> 00:04:34,980
I couldn't eat or sleep.

71
00:04:36,310 --> 00:04:39,920
I couldn't even bring myself to look at his face.

72
00:04:49,460 --> 00:04:50,530
But one day,

73
00:04:51,530 --> 00:04:53,670
he said something to me.

74
00:04:54,170 --> 00:04:55,430
Please, don't be sad anymore.

75
00:04:56,430 --> 00:04:58,240
If you keep this up, you're going to get sick, Jeong Hee.

76
00:04:59,640 --> 00:05:02,370
I couldn't tell him what I'd done,

77
00:05:03,210 --> 00:05:04,340
which only made me more miserable.

78
00:05:06,040 --> 00:05:10,620
But still, he did everything he could to comfort me.

79
00:05:11,350 --> 00:05:13,480
As we tended to each other's wounds,

80
00:05:14,420 --> 00:05:16,490
we grew closer and closer.

81
00:05:18,920 --> 00:05:21,630
And so, with our broken hearts, we got married.

82
00:05:22,730 --> 00:05:26,460
We had a child and lived that way for fifty years.

83
00:05:28,230 --> 00:05:29,730
All that time,

84
00:05:30,230 --> 00:05:33,940
he cherished me as his wife and as a mother to Ji Hoon, but...

85
00:05:35,070 --> 00:05:36,070
I...

86
00:05:37,340 --> 00:05:41,280
The guilt that I had caused the death of the woman my husband loved...

87
00:05:41,850 --> 00:05:43,510
I could never shake it.

88
00:05:46,150 --> 00:05:47,890
So I made a promise to myself.

89
00:05:48,820 --> 00:05:50,020
That someday,

90
00:05:50,860 --> 00:05:54,830
I would find Seon Hwa's son and give him what was rightfully hers.

91
00:05:56,760 --> 00:05:58,230
It was the only way...

92
00:05:59,530 --> 00:06:01,270
I could even begin to atone for my sin.

93
00:06:05,870 --> 00:06:07,640
I understand how you feel, ma'am.

94
00:06:08,340 --> 00:06:12,010
But since your husband's will was proven to be a forgery,

95
00:06:12,640 --> 00:06:15,650
the current lawsuit will be dismissed.

96
00:06:16,080 --> 00:06:17,180
Then...

97
00:06:18,420 --> 00:06:22,150
does that mean I can't give the money to Seon Hwa's son?

98
00:06:22,350 --> 00:06:26,120
I can request a settlement from the plaintiff as a goodwill gesture.

99
00:06:26,290 --> 00:06:27,760
Even that won't be easy.

100
00:06:28,430 --> 00:06:31,830
Mr. Kang Ji Hoon is likely already upset because of the forgery,

101
00:06:32,730 --> 00:06:36,670
and he'll likely refuse to acknowledge contributions from 40 years ago.

102
00:06:42,240 --> 00:06:47,110
I know this is going to sound crazy,

103
00:06:48,410 --> 00:06:49,410
but what if...

104
00:06:50,550 --> 00:06:51,550
What if...

105
00:06:52,550 --> 00:06:54,850
Seon Hwa is still alive?

106
00:06:55,520 --> 00:06:56,750
What would happen then?

107
00:06:59,090 --> 00:07:00,930
What are you talking about?

108
00:07:02,290 --> 00:07:04,530
I went to Seon Hwa's grave.

109
00:07:06,300 --> 00:07:08,930
I wanted to bury these shoes with her.

110
00:07:13,340 --> 00:07:14,340
Seon Hwa...

111
00:07:17,410 --> 00:07:19,040
I know it's far too late,

112
00:07:21,380 --> 00:07:24,320
but I feel like I have to return these to you now.

113
00:07:32,890 --> 00:07:34,490
Seon Hwa, I'm so sorry.

114
00:08:03,050 --> 00:08:06,090
(Thank you, Jeong Hee.)

115
00:08:06,320 --> 00:08:07,430
Seon Hwa?

116
00:08:10,730 --> 00:08:11,730
Seon Hwa...

117
00:08:14,130 --> 00:08:16,930
- Seon Hwa! - But that's a place...

118
00:08:18,440 --> 00:08:19,700
only my husband,

119
00:08:20,640 --> 00:08:22,970
Seon Hwa, and I knew about.

120
00:08:23,810 --> 00:08:26,710
We were the only three people who knew about that place.

121
00:08:28,480 --> 00:08:32,150
This note must have been left by Seon Hwa.

122
00:08:37,720 --> 00:08:40,690
(Thank you, Jeong Hee.)

123
00:08:43,460 --> 00:08:45,200
If Ryeo Seon Hwa is alive,

124
00:08:45,900 --> 00:08:47,470
then that changes everything.

125
00:08:49,400 --> 00:08:52,900
- Wouldn't you agree, Ms. Han? - That may be true if she is, but...

126
00:08:53,640 --> 00:08:56,810
it won't be easy to find someone who just vanished, leaving only a note.

127
00:08:57,710 --> 00:09:01,450
- I'm sorry, but I should be going. - No, wait...

128
00:09:03,850 --> 00:09:04,850
Hold on a second.

129
00:09:23,570 --> 00:09:25,370
I know you're upset and angry.

130
00:09:26,640 --> 00:09:27,740
But...

131
00:09:28,410 --> 00:09:29,740
don't you feel bad for them?

132
00:09:30,340 --> 00:09:31,540
For whom?

133
00:09:32,410 --> 00:09:33,510
All of them.

134
00:09:34,280 --> 00:09:35,710
Ms. Chae, her husband,

135
00:09:36,810 --> 00:09:38,150
and Ryeo Seon Hwa too.

136
00:09:44,720 --> 00:09:46,260
I'll go visit Taebaek.

137
00:09:47,060 --> 00:09:52,060
If they offer a settlement, we take it, and this is over. Got it?

138
00:09:55,370 --> 00:09:56,670
(Taebaek)

139
00:09:56,730 --> 00:09:58,640
Now that the will has been proven to be a forgery,

140
00:09:59,140 --> 00:10:01,340
the other party will agree to drop the lawsuit.

141
00:10:01,770 --> 00:10:05,940
If we offer a consolation payment or settlement, they'll be satisfied.

142
00:10:09,380 --> 00:10:12,750
Of course, if you prefer, sir, we don't have to give them a single cent.

143
00:10:12,920 --> 00:10:14,890
That my mother reported Ryeo Seon Hwa,

144
00:10:15,620 --> 00:10:17,660
and that she died in prison...

145
00:10:19,190 --> 00:10:20,520
Why didn't you tell me?

146
00:10:24,430 --> 00:10:27,030
I apologize for not informing you sooner, sir.

147
00:10:27,430 --> 00:10:29,500
But I was only doing it for your own good.

148
00:10:29,900 --> 00:10:32,000
I didn't want you to get caught up in any unnecessary emotions.

149
00:10:32,170 --> 00:10:33,340
Unnecessary feelings?

150
00:10:35,170 --> 00:10:37,540
Guilt, a sense of obligation, sympathy, and pity.

151
00:10:37,610 --> 00:10:40,440
You know, feelings that are unhelpful in a trial.

152
00:10:41,780 --> 00:10:43,110
Wasn't your goal from the very beginning...

153
00:10:43,280 --> 00:10:45,220
to protect your father's inheritance?

154
00:10:46,050 --> 00:10:48,450
I was simply doing everything I could to achieve that goal for you.

155
00:10:50,050 --> 00:10:53,290
What about the settlement? Do you have a figure in mind?

156
00:10:53,390 --> 00:10:56,360
I'll decide later whether to offer a settlement or consolation money.

157
00:10:57,060 --> 00:10:58,630
First, I need to go see my mother.

158
00:10:59,600 --> 00:11:00,660
I'll see you later then.

159
00:11:07,410 --> 00:11:09,210
At a time like this, he's still worried about what his mother thinks?

160
00:11:14,910 --> 00:11:17,520
Sir, Lawyer Han is here.

161
00:11:18,950 --> 00:11:19,950
Okay.

162
00:11:26,920 --> 00:11:28,160
You're here sooner than I expected.

163
00:11:29,960 --> 00:11:31,530
How's your father?

164
00:11:33,500 --> 00:11:34,730
You knew I'd come?

165
00:11:35,570 --> 00:11:37,000
Yes. Of course.

166
00:11:37,970 --> 00:11:40,840
I've even had your old office set up for you.

167
00:11:41,540 --> 00:11:45,210
Let's stop wasting time and get back to work together.

168
00:11:45,280 --> 00:11:48,680
Let's stop wasting time and get straight to the point.

169
00:11:49,880 --> 00:11:51,020
Let's drop this case.

170
00:11:56,450 --> 00:11:57,660
(Evidence for Profit Sharing Injunction)

171
00:11:57,720 --> 00:11:59,360
I know claiming one-third is a stretch.

172
00:11:59,890 --> 00:12:03,260
But Ms. Ryeo Seon Hwa clearly contributed,

173
00:12:03,390 --> 00:12:04,460
and we have plenty of evidence.

174
00:12:06,200 --> 00:12:08,630
I'd like to settle for ten percent...

175
00:12:08,730 --> 00:12:10,430
of the company's assets. What do you say?

176
00:12:13,470 --> 00:12:18,110
You valued a 40-year-old contribution against its current net worth?

177
00:12:21,680 --> 00:12:24,720
There's no way an absurd idea like that came from you.

178
00:12:25,450 --> 00:12:26,650
Was it Shin Yi Rang's idea?

179
00:12:26,720 --> 00:12:29,850
It's not absurd, and it wasn't Lawyer Shin's idea.

180
00:12:35,730 --> 00:12:37,560
The rational, level-headed Lawyer Han I knew...

181
00:12:38,360 --> 00:12:39,560
Why have you changed so much?

182
00:12:41,930 --> 00:12:45,070
You saw Shin Yi Rang pull another one of his stunts in court.

183
00:12:46,040 --> 00:12:48,470
I told you. He's dangerous to be around.

184
00:12:49,670 --> 00:12:51,510
Lawyer Han, you and Shin Yi Rang are completely different.

185
00:12:52,040 --> 00:12:54,980
You're not compatible. It's like you're two different species.

186
00:12:56,910 --> 00:12:57,920
You're right.

187
00:12:59,280 --> 00:13:01,050
Lawyer Shin and I are different people.

188
00:13:03,820 --> 00:13:05,260
And that's why I enjoy being with him.

189
00:13:07,530 --> 00:13:08,530
Then what about me?

190
00:13:09,860 --> 00:13:10,860
What?

191
00:13:12,530 --> 00:13:13,560
I mean...

192
00:13:14,130 --> 00:13:15,330
We at Taebaek...

193
00:13:16,470 --> 00:13:18,140
need a lawyer like you.

194
00:13:19,070 --> 00:13:23,140
- Taebaek has many lawyers better than me. - Whatever. Forget it.

195
00:13:24,580 --> 00:13:27,409
Come back, or the settlement is off, just so you know.

196
00:13:27,410 --> 00:13:30,080
- Why are you being so childish? - What, you didn't know about it?

197
00:13:30,610 --> 00:13:32,420
You used to tell me off for being childish all the time.

198
00:13:36,050 --> 00:13:37,050
Fine.

199
00:13:37,860 --> 00:13:39,460
If you're really not going to settle,

200
00:13:40,090 --> 00:13:41,860
then we'll just have to find another way.

201
00:13:45,360 --> 00:13:46,360
What other way?

202
00:13:48,630 --> 00:13:49,630
What?

203
00:13:56,240 --> 00:13:58,680
They have no records of Seon Hwa at the prison?

204
00:13:59,480 --> 00:14:00,480
That's right.

205
00:14:01,150 --> 00:14:05,450
Then again, it was a very long time ago.

206
00:14:07,720 --> 00:14:08,820
But...

207
00:14:09,550 --> 00:14:11,460
if Seon Hwa is still alive,

208
00:14:12,160 --> 00:14:14,460
then whose remains are in her grave?

209
00:14:15,530 --> 00:14:18,260
By the way, who gave you the remains?

210
00:14:18,800 --> 00:14:21,270
Her lawyer brought them.

211
00:14:21,730 --> 00:14:24,130
I think he said he was a public defender.

212
00:14:25,070 --> 00:14:27,740
But it was so long ago.

213
00:14:28,010 --> 00:14:31,010
I don't know his name or any of his contact info.

214
00:14:33,080 --> 00:14:34,450
I've found a way.

215
00:14:35,550 --> 00:14:36,550
Goodness.

216
00:14:36,551 --> 00:14:37,879
We can go through the bar association...

217
00:14:37,880 --> 00:14:40,020
to find a list of public defenders...

218
00:14:40,220 --> 00:14:42,120
who visited Anyang Prison around that time.

219
00:14:42,650 --> 00:14:45,290
Ryeo Seon Hwa's lawyer should be on that list.

220
00:14:54,100 --> 00:14:55,830
I take it the settlement didn't happen?

221
00:14:57,400 --> 00:15:00,270
No. We're dropping this lawsuit.

222
00:15:01,040 --> 00:15:02,870
We'll only be at a disadvantage if we continue.

223
00:15:05,010 --> 00:15:06,010
I agree.

224
00:15:06,880 --> 00:15:09,480
Instead, I'm thinking of starting a new lawsuit.

225
00:15:10,510 --> 00:15:11,720
A new lawsuit?

226
00:15:12,150 --> 00:15:14,890
We'll have Ryeo Seon Hwa's son, Cha Eun Seong, act as the plaintiff,

227
00:15:15,290 --> 00:15:16,650
and file a lawsuit...

228
00:15:16,750 --> 00:15:18,720
for an Injunction on Profit Distribution against the company.

229
00:15:21,330 --> 00:15:22,430
That could work.

230
00:15:23,290 --> 00:15:26,330
As long as we can find Ryeo Seon Hwa and get her in court,

231
00:15:26,800 --> 00:15:28,000
we'll have a fighting chance.

232
00:15:28,300 --> 00:15:29,500
Exactly.

233
00:15:33,370 --> 00:15:34,370
What a relief.

234
00:15:40,880 --> 00:15:43,180
- Sorry. - Are you tired?

235
00:15:43,380 --> 00:15:45,980
I've been drafting the complaint for the past few days,

236
00:15:46,280 --> 00:15:47,380
so I haven't gotten much sleep.

237
00:15:49,090 --> 00:15:50,090
Here.

238
00:15:51,460 --> 00:15:52,460
Want some?

239
00:15:54,660 --> 00:15:55,860
Coffee.

240
00:16:07,810 --> 00:16:09,040
That's a real eye-opener.

241
00:16:11,380 --> 00:16:12,380
It's really good.

242
00:16:13,840 --> 00:16:15,110
Maybe it's because you gave it to me.

243
00:16:20,550 --> 00:16:23,650
(Shin Yi Rang Law Office)

244
00:16:24,460 --> 00:16:27,830
Searching for public defenders...

245
00:16:28,260 --> 00:16:31,130
who visited Anyang Prison between 1983 and 1985.

246
00:16:31,600 --> 00:16:33,600
Attorney Jang Gyeong Yeop?

247
00:16:33,700 --> 00:16:35,300
(Han Na Hyun, Attorney at Law)

248
00:16:35,370 --> 00:16:37,600
By any chance, back in 1983,

249
00:16:37,670 --> 00:16:41,640
did you know an inmate at Anyang Prison named Ryeo Seon Hwa?

250
00:16:46,010 --> 00:16:48,780
We'll have to contact them one by one. This isn't working.

251
00:16:49,110 --> 00:16:50,310
That's what I was thinking.

252
00:16:54,020 --> 00:16:55,720
But while we're eating,

253
00:16:56,320 --> 00:16:57,650
let's try not to think about work.

254
00:16:58,790 --> 00:16:59,890
Sounds good.

255
00:17:01,960 --> 00:17:04,960
What should I start with?

256
00:17:15,110 --> 00:17:16,110
The eel...

257
00:17:19,710 --> 00:17:21,150
You know, I noticed this last time too.

258
00:17:21,810 --> 00:17:23,250
Our personalities are so different,

259
00:17:23,350 --> 00:17:24,620
but we have the exact same taste in food.

260
00:17:28,420 --> 00:17:29,420
Here.

261
00:17:30,250 --> 00:17:31,460
You first.

262
00:17:32,060 --> 00:17:33,520
Okay, then. One each, to be fair.

263
00:17:49,470 --> 00:17:50,570
This is really good.

264
00:18:01,790 --> 00:18:04,320
(Attorney Shin Yi Rang)

265
00:18:06,890 --> 00:18:08,160
(Attorney Shin Yi Rang)

266
00:18:38,060 --> 00:18:39,060
Yes?

267
00:18:42,360 --> 00:18:44,930
Shin Yi Rang's team has agreed to drop the case.

268
00:18:46,600 --> 00:18:48,230
As they should. What other choice did they have?

269
00:18:48,530 --> 00:18:51,640
But in its place, Cha Eun Seong has filed a suit against Ideal Shoes,

270
00:18:51,840 --> 00:18:55,040
to claim his mother Ryeo Seon Hwa's shares.

271
00:18:56,140 --> 00:18:57,140
They what?

272
00:19:03,180 --> 00:19:04,920
(The defendant shall pay the plaintiff a sum equivalent to...)

273
00:19:05,020 --> 00:19:06,880
(one-third of the current value of Ideal Shoes' shares.)

274
00:19:07,450 --> 00:19:09,220
So Han Na Hyun really wants to pick a fight?

275
00:19:14,290 --> 00:19:17,230
Go right now and find out where Ryeo Seon Hwa was buried.

276
00:19:17,690 --> 00:19:19,200
And get a DNA sample from Cha Eun Seong.

277
00:19:19,930 --> 00:19:21,830
- Excuse me? - I hear most defectors...

278
00:19:22,030 --> 00:19:23,770
from the North get in with fake identities.

279
00:19:26,840 --> 00:19:28,470
That means Ryeo Seon Hwa and Cha Eun Seong...

280
00:19:28,570 --> 00:19:30,610
might not actually be mother and son.

281
00:19:31,510 --> 00:19:34,210
And what if the test proves they are mother and son?

282
00:19:35,080 --> 00:19:36,480
Then make the results say they're not.

283
00:19:37,510 --> 00:19:39,620
Do I have to spell it out for you?

284
00:19:40,550 --> 00:19:43,090
If I have to do everything for you,

285
00:19:43,190 --> 00:19:44,860
why bother coming to work, Director Choi?

286
00:19:48,230 --> 00:19:50,560
- Don't just stand there. Get on it. - Yes, sir.

287
00:19:57,130 --> 00:19:58,140
Here you go.

288
00:20:03,610 --> 00:20:05,280
How have you been feeling?

289
00:20:05,480 --> 00:20:07,710
I've been feeling much better since I started eating your food.

290
00:20:08,410 --> 00:20:09,850
It's really nothing.

291
00:20:10,080 --> 00:20:11,680
You know what they say. Food is the best medicine.

292
00:20:13,680 --> 00:20:16,220
So, Yi Rang must be busy these days.

293
00:20:16,550 --> 00:20:21,390
Yes. He's not overwhelmed, but he's getting a lot of clients.

294
00:20:22,590 --> 00:20:23,860
I was at his last trial,

295
00:20:24,390 --> 00:20:26,200
and I got to see Yi Rang make his argument.

296
00:20:28,100 --> 00:20:29,730
He was a little unorthodox,

297
00:20:30,500 --> 00:20:31,770
but he was really compelling.

298
00:20:34,770 --> 00:20:35,970
Just like his father.

299
00:20:39,510 --> 00:20:40,980
The doctor told me...

300
00:20:42,610 --> 00:20:45,050
that my heart could stop at any moment.

301
00:20:46,280 --> 00:20:47,550
Maybe that's why I keep...

302
00:20:49,550 --> 00:20:50,890
thinking about Gi Jung.

303
00:20:52,520 --> 00:20:54,290
I feel like I might have missed something,

304
00:20:54,990 --> 00:20:56,690
and I'm starting to see some holes in the case.

305
00:20:58,500 --> 00:20:59,730
I'm left with so many regrets.

306
00:21:01,970 --> 00:21:04,770
I've told you. You don't have to do this.

307
00:21:04,840 --> 00:21:06,740
I'm doing this for my own peace of mind.

308
00:21:08,140 --> 00:21:11,140
If there's any way to clear Gi Jung's name,

309
00:21:12,640 --> 00:21:14,440
I want to do it before I die.

310
00:21:16,010 --> 00:21:17,080
By any chance...

311
00:21:18,120 --> 00:21:20,320
Are there any documents he left behind?

312
00:21:21,220 --> 00:21:23,750
- Documents? - Yes. You know what he was like.

313
00:21:24,450 --> 00:21:26,790
Gi Jung always took such meticulous notes.

314
00:21:27,660 --> 00:21:31,230
But his notebook on the case...

315
00:21:31,800 --> 00:21:34,200
and other key files were nowhere to be found.

316
00:21:34,900 --> 00:21:35,900
So,

317
00:21:36,500 --> 00:21:39,370
I was wondering if maybe he kept them somewhere else.

318
00:21:41,000 --> 00:21:42,010
I don't know.

319
00:21:43,540 --> 00:21:46,910
I have a box of my husband's old papers at home, but...

320
00:21:48,310 --> 00:21:50,010
I didn't see any case files in there.

321
00:21:50,410 --> 00:21:52,220
And I don't recall seeing a notebook, either.

322
00:21:54,820 --> 00:21:55,820
I see.

323
00:22:03,730 --> 00:22:05,700
(Attorney Shin Yi Rang)

324
00:22:05,760 --> 00:22:08,730
(Petition for Provisional Injunction on Profit Distribution)

325
00:22:19,010 --> 00:22:21,010
(Attorney Han Na Hyun)

326
00:22:42,600 --> 00:22:44,630
(Last will and Testament, Testator: Kang Dong Sik)

327
00:22:44,740 --> 00:22:45,940
(Manri-dong in 1980, Manri-dong in 2025)

328
00:22:47,540 --> 00:22:51,440
(Executor: Chae Jeong Hee, The 3 co-founders)

329
00:22:55,810 --> 00:22:59,080
(Thank you, Jeong Hee.)

330
00:22:59,350 --> 00:23:00,720
It seems Ms. Ryeo Seon Hwa left that letter...

331
00:23:01,350 --> 00:23:04,250
because she knew what Ms. Chae wanted.

332
00:23:05,490 --> 00:23:07,360
So why would she be in hiding?

333
00:23:08,790 --> 00:23:11,130
Keeping it a secret even from her own son.

334
00:23:11,900 --> 00:23:14,560
Normally, for shoes to be comfortable,

335
00:23:15,230 --> 00:23:16,870
they need to be soft.

336
00:23:17,570 --> 00:23:22,610
But in a dangerous place like a construction site,

337
00:23:23,240 --> 00:23:26,310
it's the uncomfortable, hard-toed boots...

338
00:23:26,910 --> 00:23:29,910
that keep your feet safe.

339
00:23:31,380 --> 00:23:32,450
Pardon?

340
00:23:33,020 --> 00:23:34,680
I don't know who this woman is,

341
00:23:35,350 --> 00:23:40,520
but maybe she's hiding inside a pair of hard-toed boots.

342
00:23:42,160 --> 00:23:43,660
You mean, to keep herself safe?

343
00:23:44,690 --> 00:23:45,700
Exactly.

344
00:23:55,670 --> 00:23:57,170
(From Lee Jeong Su)

345
00:23:58,980 --> 00:24:00,180
(I'm responding to your email.)

346
00:24:02,110 --> 00:24:03,110
(Regarding the time you asked about,)

347
00:24:03,110 --> 00:24:04,110
(I remember an inmate at Anyang Prison...)

348
00:24:04,150 --> 00:24:05,150
(named Ryeo Seon Hwa.)

349
00:24:10,120 --> 00:24:12,460
Hello? I'm calling in response to your email.

350
00:24:15,930 --> 00:24:17,190
Yes, that's right. About Ms. Ryeo Seon Hwa.

351
00:24:21,600 --> 00:24:23,230
It says Attorney Lee Jeong Su...

352
00:24:23,800 --> 00:24:26,200
spent his entire career as a public defender.

353
00:24:27,370 --> 00:24:30,640
He retired a long time ago, and he's battling terminal cancer.

354
00:24:31,440 --> 00:24:33,680
We might be coming back empty-handed, then.

355
00:24:34,110 --> 00:24:36,010
No, if that was his intention,

356
00:24:36,310 --> 00:24:38,350
he wouldn't have reached out to us in the first place.

357
00:24:41,650 --> 00:24:44,220
(Garam Hospice)

358
00:24:47,460 --> 00:24:50,790
Ms. Ryeo Seon Hwa was parted from her son when he was just one year old.

359
00:24:51,260 --> 00:24:54,660
Do you happen to remember anything about her?

360
00:24:55,930 --> 00:24:57,400
She was a woman of few words.

361
00:24:58,170 --> 00:24:59,770
A quiet person.

362
00:25:01,140 --> 00:25:05,180
But you could tell she was a principled and upright person.

363
00:25:06,480 --> 00:25:08,080
But that's all I know.

364
00:25:09,050 --> 00:25:11,850
If you want to know more,

365
00:25:12,680 --> 00:25:15,290
you should talk to the other inmates. The ones who were with her.

366
00:25:15,820 --> 00:25:17,620
That would be your best bet.

367
00:25:18,590 --> 00:25:23,230
We considered that, but the prison no longer has the records.

368
00:25:24,190 --> 00:25:28,600
I represented another female inmate.

369
00:25:29,700 --> 00:25:34,100
I recall she shared a cell with Ryeo Seon Hwa.

370
00:25:34,440 --> 00:25:36,610
Do you happen to remember her name?

371
00:25:40,810 --> 00:25:42,080
Open that for me.

372
00:25:43,850 --> 00:25:46,850
- This? - Yes, in that notebook.

373
00:25:47,950 --> 00:25:49,590
Her phone number should be in there.

374
00:25:54,490 --> 00:25:57,790
- Thank you, Counselor. - No, thank you.

375
00:25:59,430 --> 00:26:00,930
For letting me...

376
00:26:01,100 --> 00:26:04,530
do one good thing for Ms. Ryeo Seon Hwa before I go.

377
00:26:07,370 --> 00:26:10,170
(Garam Hospice)

378
00:26:11,210 --> 00:26:14,910
Bong Soo is great at finding people. I'll give him a call.

379
00:26:17,080 --> 00:26:20,380
Honey, how can you just leave like this?

380
00:26:21,020 --> 00:26:23,590
What are Ji Ah and I supposed to do?

381
00:26:24,420 --> 00:26:25,590
I'm sorry...

382
00:26:26,360 --> 00:26:27,960
I wanted to be there for you until the end...

383
00:26:39,740 --> 00:26:41,070
Where's that coming from?

384
00:26:41,770 --> 00:26:42,770
Where is...

385
00:26:45,880 --> 00:26:46,880
Cut!

386
00:26:47,540 --> 00:26:51,180
What is that noise? Whose phone is that?

387
00:26:51,480 --> 00:26:53,880
- Whose phone is it? - It's not me.

388
00:26:54,280 --> 00:26:57,220
- Darn it. - What is this?

389
00:26:57,550 --> 00:27:00,160
- That's it over there. - Here. This one. Whose phone is this?

390
00:27:00,960 --> 00:27:03,330
- Seriously? Who is it? - It just came out of nowhere...

391
00:27:05,430 --> 00:27:08,670
All right. Thanks to you, I got kicked clean off the set,

392
00:27:08,900 --> 00:27:10,270
so I'll look into it for you as soon as I leave.

393
00:27:33,520 --> 00:27:34,520
I've found it.

394
00:27:35,130 --> 00:27:36,289
At the place where CEO Kang's driver said...

395
00:27:36,290 --> 00:27:38,030
he'd occasionally take Ms. Chae,

396
00:27:38,160 --> 00:27:40,000
we found a burial mound that appears to be Ryeo Seon Hwa's grave.

397
00:27:40,960 --> 00:27:42,370
Request an autopsy from the court...

398
00:27:42,570 --> 00:27:45,170
and get Cha Eun Seong's DNA immediately.

399
00:27:46,070 --> 00:27:47,300
A DNA test?

400
00:27:50,810 --> 00:27:53,010
I understand. I'll call you back.

401
00:28:05,560 --> 00:28:08,560
Taebaek has requested a paternity test.

402
00:28:09,190 --> 00:28:12,360
It looks like CEO Yang has found where Ms. Ryeo Seon Hwa is buried.

403
00:28:13,630 --> 00:28:15,170
That was a smart move.

404
00:28:15,630 --> 00:28:19,240
This may be a lawsuit for an injunction on profit distribution,

405
00:28:19,600 --> 00:28:21,910
but it's essentially an inheritance dispute.

406
00:28:22,340 --> 00:28:25,340
If Ms. Chae is right and Ryeo Seon Hwa is still alive,

407
00:28:25,640 --> 00:28:27,840
then the DNA test won't be a match.

408
00:28:29,610 --> 00:28:32,480
But it's not like we can refuse the test.

409
00:28:34,920 --> 00:28:38,320
The only way to win now is to find Ryeo Seon Hwa.

410
00:28:38,720 --> 00:28:40,190
Have you heard from Bong Soo?

411
00:28:40,360 --> 00:28:43,460
Yes, he said he found her current number and spoke with her.

412
00:28:44,130 --> 00:28:45,660
And she knows Ms. Ryeo Seon Hwa?

413
00:28:45,760 --> 00:28:47,800
Yes, she said they served time together.

414
00:28:48,770 --> 00:28:51,430
He's on his way, so we should get going.

415
00:28:51,630 --> 00:28:52,670
Okay.

416
00:29:34,410 --> 00:29:38,310
Who are you? Why seek someone dead for over 40 years?

417
00:29:40,450 --> 00:29:42,120
My name is Shin Yi Rang. I'm a lawyer.

418
00:29:43,250 --> 00:29:46,790
Ryeo Seon Hwa's son is curious about his mother.

419
00:29:47,160 --> 00:29:49,430
I never heard she had a son.

420
00:29:50,760 --> 00:29:54,000
Then again, she was always full of secrets.

421
00:29:55,170 --> 00:30:00,300
About how Ryeo Seon Hwa passed away... Could you tell me the details?

422
00:30:02,040 --> 00:30:04,640
There was a fire in the prison laundry.

423
00:30:06,210 --> 00:30:10,150
Seon Hwa and Sun Young were taken to the hospital with burns,

424
00:30:10,910 --> 00:30:13,150
but neither of them ever came back.

425
00:30:13,550 --> 00:30:16,790
So does that mean they both died?

426
00:30:20,490 --> 00:30:22,160
Only Seon Hwa died.

427
00:30:22,730 --> 00:30:25,760
Sun Young was treated at the hospital for a few weeks...

428
00:30:26,600 --> 00:30:28,900
and was released from there when her sentence was up.

429
00:30:31,370 --> 00:30:33,770
Are you still in contact with this Sun Young?

430
00:30:34,540 --> 00:30:35,540
No.

431
00:30:37,070 --> 00:30:39,140
We didn't exactly part as friends.

432
00:30:52,920 --> 00:30:54,890
Lawyer Shin, are you thinking what I'm thinking?

433
00:30:55,990 --> 00:30:59,200
That Sun Young might actually be Ryeo Seon Hwa?

434
00:31:01,160 --> 00:31:05,570
If Ryeo Seon Hwa is really alive, I'd say the chances are high.

435
00:31:17,310 --> 00:31:19,920
If they both suffered facial burns,

436
00:31:20,550 --> 00:31:22,590
and considering this was 50 years ago,

437
00:31:23,350 --> 00:31:26,060
they could've just swapped prison uniforms and fooled everyone.

438
00:31:27,560 --> 00:31:30,430
Especially if the fire destroyed all the records.

439
00:31:30,930 --> 00:31:32,130
It would've been even easier.

440
00:31:32,330 --> 00:31:35,030
All we have to do is find this woman, Sun Young...

441
00:31:35,970 --> 00:31:37,400
But where would we even find her?

442
00:31:40,070 --> 00:31:41,070
That's the question.

443
00:31:42,940 --> 00:31:45,580
Wait. Where did he go?

444
00:32:08,330 --> 00:32:11,130
She seems like such a good, humble person.

445
00:32:15,270 --> 00:32:17,240
But why was she shaking her leg?

446
00:32:18,880 --> 00:32:20,740
Was she anxious about something?

447
00:32:27,450 --> 00:32:29,020
(Eunseon Noodles)

448
00:32:29,550 --> 00:32:30,550
(Park Sun Young)

449
00:32:36,930 --> 00:32:38,960
Hello? Seon Hwa?

450
00:32:40,130 --> 00:32:43,400
There are some people looking for you. You have to get out of there. Now.

451
00:32:46,970 --> 00:32:49,640
Wait a minute. That is Seon Hwa!

452
00:32:50,870 --> 00:32:53,480
It's her! Oh, my...

453
00:32:57,980 --> 00:32:59,550
There he is.

454
00:33:00,520 --> 00:33:01,550
Let's go. Hurry.

455
00:33:03,150 --> 00:33:05,290
- Let's go. - Go where?

456
00:33:05,590 --> 00:33:09,430
The noodle shop. Seon Hwa's there.

457
00:33:10,160 --> 00:33:12,760
- Really? - What? What did he say?

458
00:33:13,300 --> 00:33:15,330
He said Ryeo Seon Hwa is at the noodle shop.

459
00:33:16,030 --> 00:33:18,700
Why would Ryeo Seon Hwa be at the noodle shop?

460
00:33:21,740 --> 00:33:25,210
You're having a late lunch. You can't go around skipping meals.

461
00:33:26,040 --> 00:33:29,310
Stop by anytime, it doesn't matter when. Okay?

462
00:33:30,050 --> 00:33:32,180
All right, eat up.

463
00:33:32,880 --> 00:33:33,880
Ma'am.

464
00:33:42,090 --> 00:33:43,360
- The noodle shop lady? - The noodle shop lady?

465
00:33:48,600 --> 00:33:52,670
Seon Hwa. Please don't run from me.

466
00:33:53,940 --> 00:33:56,870
You have to at least let me apologize.

467
00:34:19,900 --> 00:34:22,130
(Eunseon Noodles)

468
00:34:34,040 --> 00:34:35,040
Anyone here?

469
00:34:36,250 --> 00:34:37,450
Hello? Is anybody in there?

470
00:34:38,710 --> 00:34:39,820
Lawyer Shin?

471
00:34:41,050 --> 00:34:44,120
Mr. Cha. Was the owner not in today?

472
00:34:45,020 --> 00:34:46,760
No, she was here.

473
00:34:47,360 --> 00:34:49,660
She was busy with customers right through lunch.

474
00:34:49,760 --> 00:34:52,090
Then she suddenly closed up shop and rushed out.

475
00:34:53,330 --> 00:34:55,800
- She rushed out? - Yes.

476
00:35:09,050 --> 00:35:11,910
When did she leave? She just left, right?

477
00:35:12,250 --> 00:35:16,820
- Yes. What's this all about? - I'll explain later.

478
00:35:17,390 --> 00:35:18,490
For now, let's go.

479
00:35:20,960 --> 00:35:25,259
- Yi Rang! - Bong Soo! Turn around! Back up!

480
00:35:25,260 --> 00:35:26,360
Back up? Back up where?

481
00:35:26,930 --> 00:35:29,570
- No time to explain. Just follow us! - Okay.

482
00:35:38,840 --> 00:35:40,410
Ms. Choi Gil Ja must have called her.

483
00:35:40,910 --> 00:35:43,580
Why would she go to such lengths to hide?

484
00:35:50,690 --> 00:35:51,750
Which way should I go?

485
00:35:53,060 --> 00:35:55,560
We'll go left. You take the right.

486
00:35:55,930 --> 00:35:56,930
Got it.

487
00:36:11,440 --> 00:36:14,180
There were no turn-offs. Did she go left?

488
00:36:24,090 --> 00:36:26,220
There she is! Over there!

489
00:36:32,700 --> 00:36:34,600
(Hwayang River)

490
00:36:53,880 --> 00:36:54,880
Do we...

491
00:36:55,620 --> 00:36:56,890
have the right to do this?

492
00:36:59,120 --> 00:37:02,290
She went through so much and barely made it back alive.

493
00:37:03,060 --> 00:37:05,190
She's just a mother secretly making meals for her son.

494
00:37:06,530 --> 00:37:09,670
If it weren't for us... she could be with her son.

495
00:37:10,630 --> 00:37:12,000
But we're the ones chasing her away.

496
00:37:13,240 --> 00:37:16,470
Do we really have that right?

497
00:37:17,940 --> 00:37:19,380
I understand where you're coming from, Lawyer Shin.

498
00:37:24,480 --> 00:37:26,180
In that case, let me go talk to her alone.

499
00:37:26,950 --> 00:37:30,650
I'll just ask what she wants to do. If she says no, I'll let her go.

500
00:37:56,880 --> 00:37:58,080
Hello.

501
00:37:59,920 --> 00:38:00,920
Who are you?

502
00:38:02,020 --> 00:38:03,590
My name is Han Na Hyun. I'm a lawyer.

503
00:38:05,090 --> 00:38:06,420
You're Ryeo Seon Hwa, aren't you?

504
00:38:08,390 --> 00:38:09,390
You're mistaken.

505
00:38:09,890 --> 00:38:12,730
- You have the wrong person. - You were alive all this time. So why...

506
00:38:14,100 --> 00:38:15,970
Why have you been living as if you were dead?

507
00:38:17,570 --> 00:38:18,970
Even deceiving your own son.

508
00:38:23,040 --> 00:38:24,470
You seem to be looking for someone.

509
00:38:26,040 --> 00:38:29,480
Don't you think that person might have her reasons?

510
00:38:30,380 --> 00:38:32,050
Everyone has their reasons.

511
00:38:34,450 --> 00:38:35,790
Ms. Chae Jeong Hee certainly did too.

512
00:38:38,120 --> 00:38:40,290
Chae Jeong Hee wanted to give Cha Eun Seong...

513
00:38:40,790 --> 00:38:42,660
shares in Ideal Group.

514
00:38:43,290 --> 00:38:44,730
To do it, she had her husband with dementia...

515
00:38:45,190 --> 00:38:47,060
write a fake will.

516
00:38:48,430 --> 00:38:50,470
A fake will? Jeong Hee did that?

517
00:38:54,200 --> 00:38:58,140
Because she believed she was the reason you died.

518
00:38:59,880 --> 00:39:01,810
She believed that because of what she told the police,

519
00:39:02,180 --> 00:39:04,410
you were arrested.

520
00:39:05,310 --> 00:39:07,080
And she has spent 50 years atoning for it.

521
00:39:10,020 --> 00:39:12,020
I wanted to make sure I told you that.

522
00:39:15,760 --> 00:39:19,230
I'll just pretend I never saw you, then.

523
00:39:21,600 --> 00:39:22,800
Wait. Just a minute.

524
00:39:31,640 --> 00:39:32,640
Ma'am.

525
00:39:33,240 --> 00:39:34,240
Oh, my.

526
00:39:36,050 --> 00:39:37,050
We found her.

527
00:39:39,080 --> 00:39:42,080
We found Ryeo Seon Hwa. I'm telling you, we found her.

528
00:40:02,840 --> 00:40:05,670
(Shin Yi Rang and Han Na Hyun Law Office)

529
00:40:07,580 --> 00:40:08,580
Wait, hold on.

530
00:40:18,820 --> 00:40:20,490
(Shin Yi Rang and Han Na Hyun Law Office)

531
00:40:37,370 --> 00:40:38,370
Seon Hwa.

532
00:40:39,580 --> 00:40:43,510
- Jeong Hee. - Seon Hwa. You're alive.

533
00:40:45,920 --> 00:40:48,380
I thought you were dead.

534
00:40:49,950 --> 00:40:51,320
I didn't die.

535
00:40:52,790 --> 00:40:54,320
I couldn't let myself die.

536
00:40:56,530 --> 00:40:57,530
Seon Hwa.

537
00:41:00,130 --> 00:41:01,130
I'm so sorry.

538
00:41:02,230 --> 00:41:03,370
I'm so sorry, Seon Hwa.

539
00:41:04,900 --> 00:41:07,270
It's my fault. It's all my fault you...

540
00:41:07,940 --> 00:41:11,770
Seon Hwa, I'm so, so sorry. I was so foolish.

541
00:41:12,810 --> 00:41:15,810
No, it's not your fault, Jeong Hee.

542
00:41:17,880 --> 00:41:21,820
The lawyer told me everything. She told me about your misunderstanding.

543
00:41:23,750 --> 00:41:27,260
I came here to clear up that misunderstanding.

544
00:41:28,020 --> 00:41:29,090
A misunderstanding?

545
00:41:42,500 --> 00:41:44,140
Long before you were at the bar...

546
00:41:44,840 --> 00:41:46,780
and met with that police officer,

547
00:41:47,440 --> 00:41:49,980
I already knew there were people watching me.

548
00:41:52,950 --> 00:41:56,420
I was leaving after getting the letter from my son, who was defecting.

549
00:42:00,160 --> 00:42:01,760
But they got to me before the letter did.

550
00:42:02,490 --> 00:42:04,330
So, what I'm saying is, even if it wasn't you,

551
00:42:05,130 --> 00:42:07,200
I was fated to be caught no matter what.

552
00:42:07,930 --> 00:42:09,000
Seon Hwa.

553
00:42:12,470 --> 00:42:14,140
But still... I'm so sorry.

554
00:42:14,870 --> 00:42:16,110
I'm so sorry.

555
00:42:17,270 --> 00:42:21,080
Thank you. Thank you for being alive, Seon Hwa.

556
00:42:27,950 --> 00:42:30,120
Sorry I wasn't much help.

557
00:42:31,450 --> 00:42:32,450
Not at all.

558
00:42:32,920 --> 00:42:36,030
It was your idea to look for Ryeo Seon Hwa, Yi Rang.

559
00:42:36,660 --> 00:42:39,700
You deserve a lot of credit for them making up.

560
00:42:40,030 --> 00:42:41,530
Come on, that's not true.

561
00:42:41,830 --> 00:42:44,000
You're the one who convinced Ms. Ryeo Seon Hwa, Na Hyun.

562
00:42:44,330 --> 00:42:46,070
You deserve way more credit.

563
00:42:47,470 --> 00:42:48,670
Fine, I'll take the credit.

564
00:42:51,410 --> 00:42:52,910
So where's Mr. Kang now?

565
00:42:55,440 --> 00:42:56,650
He's over there.

566
00:42:58,880 --> 00:43:01,520
He would be so happy if he knew what happened today.

567
00:43:04,350 --> 00:43:06,060
But does he really need to know?

568
00:43:08,260 --> 00:43:11,890
He is still living in the past,

569
00:43:12,560 --> 00:43:13,760
back when he was 20 and in his prime.

570
00:43:22,270 --> 00:43:23,640
It's so pretty.

571
00:43:35,120 --> 00:43:37,950
Then, shall we go wrap up the trial?

572
00:43:39,960 --> 00:43:40,960
Sounds good.

573
00:43:55,640 --> 00:43:59,840
So you mean Ryeo Seon Hwa has been living as someone else,

574
00:44:00,610 --> 00:44:03,580
and if the trial continues, her true identity might be exposed?

575
00:44:04,010 --> 00:44:05,010
Yes.

576
00:44:05,550 --> 00:44:08,420
Yang Do Kyung is the kind of man who will stop at nothing...

577
00:44:08,880 --> 00:44:10,450
to get what he wants.

578
00:44:11,720 --> 00:44:13,289
On top of that, if he finds out that...

579
00:44:13,290 --> 00:44:15,260
Ryeo Seon Hwa is using a stolen identity,

580
00:44:15,920 --> 00:44:18,530
he'll use it to turn the trial in his favor.

581
00:44:19,730 --> 00:44:21,500
Why are you telling me this?

582
00:44:22,630 --> 00:44:25,530
Have you forgotten that I'm the defendant in this case?

583
00:44:28,470 --> 00:44:31,940
I thought you were someone I could reason with.

584
00:44:33,280 --> 00:44:35,810
Because I know you very well,

585
00:44:36,310 --> 00:44:37,410
Mr. Kang.

586
00:44:40,880 --> 00:44:42,280
You know me well?

587
00:44:43,490 --> 00:44:44,490
Yes.

588
00:44:44,920 --> 00:44:48,520
Someone told me what kind of person you are.

589
00:44:51,160 --> 00:44:55,660
- I see you've met my mother. - No. It was someone else.

590
00:44:58,030 --> 00:44:59,130
That person said...

591
00:44:59,870 --> 00:45:02,640
that shoes carry the warmth of their maker.

592
00:45:04,270 --> 00:45:06,180
The warmth in your shoes...

593
00:45:07,180 --> 00:45:08,780
is a reflection of your own heart.

594
00:45:12,920 --> 00:45:13,950
Here, let me see.

595
00:45:22,990 --> 00:45:25,130
What a warm shoe.

596
00:45:26,860 --> 00:45:31,200
- Pardon? - You made a shoe that shows your heart.

597
00:45:33,270 --> 00:45:36,210
Because a shoe always carries...

598
00:45:36,610 --> 00:45:38,770
the warmth of its maker.

599
00:45:42,410 --> 00:45:43,850
You're even better than me, son.

600
00:45:44,610 --> 00:45:45,610
Here.

601
00:45:47,780 --> 00:45:48,780
Thank you.

602
00:46:12,940 --> 00:46:13,940
Let's go.

603
00:46:28,860 --> 00:46:31,360
(DNA test results: Ryeo Seon Hwa, Cha Eun Seong)

604
00:46:31,790 --> 00:46:32,930
What did I tell you?

605
00:46:33,730 --> 00:46:34,960
If you wanted,

606
00:46:35,230 --> 00:46:37,600
I could make it so Cha Eun Seong wouldn't get a dime.

607
00:46:38,830 --> 00:46:39,900
You won.

608
00:46:43,270 --> 00:46:45,540
I'm dropping the lawsuit.

609
00:46:47,010 --> 00:46:48,010
What?

610
00:46:49,380 --> 00:46:51,850
Wait, you're not dropping it. We've already won.

611
00:46:52,110 --> 00:46:54,580
I had Cha Eun Seong's factory leather analyzed.

612
00:46:55,250 --> 00:46:59,150
Results show it was made with a process 100 percent identical to ours.

613
00:47:00,360 --> 00:47:03,230
Cha Eun Seong told me he produces his leather...

614
00:47:03,730 --> 00:47:05,090
with a method passed down in his family.

615
00:47:08,630 --> 00:47:09,830
Rather than this piece of paper...

616
00:47:12,000 --> 00:47:13,870
I'm choosing to believe in Cha Eun Seong's leather.

617
00:47:14,970 --> 00:47:16,170
Thank you for your efforts.

618
00:47:16,970 --> 00:47:19,070
I'll have your fee wired to you immediately.

619
00:47:40,300 --> 00:47:41,859
Hey, that's enough looking.

620
00:47:41,860 --> 00:47:44,330
You know all my stuff is good without checking.

621
00:47:45,330 --> 00:47:46,370
Gosh, a bug.

622
00:47:46,500 --> 00:47:49,610
What bug? That just means it's organic, you know?

623
00:47:49,940 --> 00:47:54,640
When you don't use pesticides, the bugs are naturally drawn to it, right?

624
00:47:54,710 --> 00:47:55,910
Gosh, but still...

625
00:47:56,580 --> 00:47:57,910
I'll take some spinach too, please.

626
00:47:58,210 --> 00:47:59,620
Of course. Good choice.

627
00:48:00,650 --> 00:48:01,719
You're buying some too, Na Hyun?

628
00:48:01,720 --> 00:48:03,590
Yes, it looks so fresh and delicious.

629
00:48:04,450 --> 00:48:07,860
Here. Let me just add...

630
00:48:08,660 --> 00:48:10,890
a little something extra.

631
00:48:11,490 --> 00:48:14,660
- Thank you. - What? Ma'am.

632
00:48:14,760 --> 00:48:15,760
What is it?

633
00:48:16,230 --> 00:48:17,500
What's the special occasion?

634
00:48:17,900 --> 00:48:19,170
Ji Hoon...

635
00:48:21,040 --> 00:48:24,670
He signed a leather supply contract with Seon Hwa's son.

636
00:48:26,710 --> 00:48:29,750
And it's all thanks to you lawyers.

637
00:48:31,380 --> 00:48:33,550
- That's great news. - Thank you.

638
00:48:35,420 --> 00:48:39,350
Oh, right. Today, Seon Hwa and I...

639
00:48:39,790 --> 00:48:41,460
are supposed to go see my husband.

640
00:48:44,360 --> 00:48:48,100
Seon Hwa...

641
00:48:48,630 --> 00:48:50,600
Wait. That's not right. She said she wasn't Seon Hwa, didn't she?

642
00:48:51,030 --> 00:48:52,030
That's not right.

643
00:48:54,870 --> 00:48:57,710
Hey, Sun Young, I'm heading out now.

644
00:49:04,610 --> 00:49:06,920
I'll be leaving soon too.

645
00:49:12,720 --> 00:49:16,160
- Where are you off to? - Just have to take care of something.

646
00:49:16,790 --> 00:49:20,760
For a second, I was worried you'd just leave like you did before.

647
00:49:21,300 --> 00:49:22,730
You were worried about me?

648
00:49:23,600 --> 00:49:24,600
Why?

649
00:49:26,940 --> 00:49:27,940
Just because.

650
00:49:29,000 --> 00:49:32,410
When I see you, you remind me of my mom.

651
00:49:36,850 --> 00:49:38,080
You remember your mom?

652
00:49:40,920 --> 00:49:43,690
We were separated when I was too young, so I don't remember her face,

653
00:49:45,850 --> 00:49:47,360
but when I eat your noodles,

654
00:49:48,760 --> 00:49:50,330
it feels like my mom's cooking.

655
00:49:51,990 --> 00:49:53,200
I see.

656
00:49:55,530 --> 00:49:56,730
Actually, for me too.

657
00:49:58,630 --> 00:49:59,970
When I see you,

658
00:50:01,270 --> 00:50:03,070
you remind me so much of my son.

659
00:50:05,410 --> 00:50:06,610
You have a son?

660
00:50:07,510 --> 00:50:08,510
I do.

661
00:50:10,710 --> 00:50:12,250
We were separated when he was young,

662
00:50:13,250 --> 00:50:15,080
and he'd be about your age now.

663
00:50:21,860 --> 00:50:23,630
Well... Listen.

664
00:50:25,360 --> 00:50:28,460
I believe people can be family even if they're not related by blood.

665
00:50:30,500 --> 00:50:32,399
I'm not trying to impose or anything,

666
00:50:32,400 --> 00:50:34,540
but we could eat holiday meals together,

667
00:50:34,670 --> 00:50:36,410
celebrate birthdays together,

668
00:50:36,510 --> 00:50:38,370
and help each other when we're sick. That kind of thing.

669
00:50:44,280 --> 00:50:46,880
I must have said too much.

670
00:50:52,390 --> 00:50:53,490
I'd like that.

671
00:50:55,720 --> 00:50:56,730
You would?

672
00:50:57,790 --> 00:50:58,990
I said I'd like that.

673
00:51:03,060 --> 00:51:06,440
From now on, just call me Eun Seong.

674
00:51:09,240 --> 00:51:10,240
Eun Seong.

675
00:51:13,880 --> 00:51:14,980
Let's take good care of each other.

676
00:51:16,240 --> 00:51:18,750
Yes, let's.

677
00:51:20,850 --> 00:51:21,850
Mom.

678
00:51:38,800 --> 00:51:39,800
Yes?

679
00:51:41,200 --> 00:51:44,270
Okay. Got it.

680
00:51:46,070 --> 00:51:49,240
- She's here, in the restroom. - I see.

681
00:51:50,180 --> 00:51:52,380
- There she is. - Oh, yes.

682
00:51:52,810 --> 00:51:54,720
I hope it goes well. I'll wait here.

683
00:51:55,920 --> 00:51:58,890
Thanks for bringing me.

684
00:52:01,060 --> 00:52:02,060
We'll be back.

685
00:52:13,800 --> 00:52:14,900
Honey.

686
00:52:15,940 --> 00:52:17,510
Seon Hwa is here.

687
00:52:26,310 --> 00:52:27,450
Dong Sik.

688
00:52:28,750 --> 00:52:30,350
I'm too late, aren't I?

689
00:52:31,950 --> 00:52:32,950
I'm so sorry.

690
00:52:35,560 --> 00:52:36,990
You must be happy, right?

691
00:52:38,560 --> 00:52:41,230
Getting to see her face, even if it's like this.

692
00:52:45,700 --> 00:52:46,770
Seon Hwa,

693
00:52:48,300 --> 00:52:52,110
I have something for you.

694
00:53:05,250 --> 00:53:06,760
Actually, to be exact,

695
00:53:07,560 --> 00:53:09,860
it's not from me. It's from Dong Sik.

696
00:53:13,130 --> 00:53:16,430
These aren't mine.

697
00:53:20,200 --> 00:53:21,300
Seon Hwa.

698
00:53:22,170 --> 00:53:23,610
It's all right.

699
00:53:25,270 --> 00:53:30,810
I saw the two of you at the workshop that day.

700
00:53:31,450 --> 00:53:33,950
No, that's not... It's just...

701
00:53:36,220 --> 00:53:37,850
All right. Here, take a look.

702
00:53:38,720 --> 00:53:39,720
Here you go.

703
00:53:43,330 --> 00:53:46,460
- Why are these so tight? - Gosh.

704
00:53:47,230 --> 00:53:51,470
- Try them on, Jeong Hee. Come on. - But I...

705
00:53:52,800 --> 00:53:54,870
- Me? - Go on.

706
00:54:41,550 --> 00:54:42,850
So cool.

707
00:55:03,440 --> 00:55:04,640
So beautiful.

708
00:55:07,640 --> 00:55:08,640
Jeong Hee.

709
00:55:09,710 --> 00:55:10,850
Dong Sik.

710
00:55:15,380 --> 00:55:17,850
You're finally wearing them. Your shoes.

711
00:55:19,050 --> 00:55:20,260
I didn't know.

712
00:55:22,490 --> 00:55:24,160
I thought they were Seon Hwa's.

713
00:55:25,060 --> 00:55:28,860
You know how your heels are delicate and get blisters easily?

714
00:55:30,000 --> 00:55:33,370
That's why I specifically asked Seon Hwa to use very soft leather.

715
00:55:37,670 --> 00:55:38,670
So these...

716
00:55:41,110 --> 00:55:42,380
These are really my shoes?

717
00:55:51,320 --> 00:55:54,690
I made them, hoping they would always bring you back home.

718
00:55:56,160 --> 00:55:59,530
And know that I would always be there waiting for you.

719
00:56:01,230 --> 00:56:02,460
That's what I wanted to tell you.

720
00:56:05,370 --> 00:56:06,900
And I had no idea...

721
00:56:07,900 --> 00:56:08,900
Jeong Hee.

722
00:56:11,110 --> 00:56:14,910
I wanted to give you the moon and the stars,

723
00:56:15,910 --> 00:56:17,580
my lovely Chae Jeong Hee.

724
00:56:21,620 --> 00:56:22,620
I loved you.

725
00:56:24,850 --> 00:56:25,850
And...

726
00:56:28,720 --> 00:56:29,860
I still love you.

727
00:57:06,560 --> 00:57:07,600
Thank you.

728
00:57:09,160 --> 00:57:11,100
You've been a great help.

729
00:57:12,830 --> 00:57:13,840
Don't mention it.

730
00:57:15,540 --> 00:57:17,840
I've seen the person I needed to see...

731
00:57:18,810 --> 00:57:24,610
and given her what I had to. So now, please let me go.

732
00:57:27,950 --> 00:57:30,150
What? You mean right here?

733
00:57:31,490 --> 00:57:33,690
Why? Can't I?

734
00:57:34,320 --> 00:57:38,690
The Father is waiting for you on the rooftop.

735
00:57:39,560 --> 00:57:41,930
I like it here just fine.

736
00:57:43,330 --> 00:57:46,300
I got to see my wife looking so happy.

737
00:57:47,070 --> 00:57:50,610
I'll have no regrets passing on from here.

738
00:57:53,680 --> 00:57:54,680
Okay.

739
00:58:00,010 --> 00:58:03,849
Father, you can burn the talisman now.

740
00:58:03,850 --> 00:58:06,050
(Father, you can burn the talisman now.)

741
00:58:07,090 --> 00:58:08,090
All right.

742
00:58:24,840 --> 00:58:25,840
Mr. Kang.

743
00:58:27,180 --> 00:58:29,380
There's one last thing I'd like to ask you.

744
00:58:30,650 --> 00:58:31,650
What is it?

745
00:58:33,450 --> 00:58:36,820
How much do you actually remember?

746
00:58:39,020 --> 00:58:41,960
Sometimes, it seems like you don't remember anything at all,

747
00:58:42,860 --> 00:58:45,860
and other times, it's like you know everything.

748
00:58:46,360 --> 00:58:50,100
There's only one thing I remember.

749
00:58:55,040 --> 00:58:56,270
Chae Jeong Hee.

750
00:58:57,470 --> 00:58:58,740
Just her.

751
00:59:02,880 --> 00:59:07,120
And that's why I remember everything.

752
00:59:09,050 --> 00:59:11,950
If you remember the one you love,

753
00:59:12,890 --> 00:59:15,620
you remember everything.

754
00:59:21,300 --> 00:59:22,300
I see.

755
00:59:30,410 --> 00:59:31,440
Sir.

756
00:59:32,410 --> 00:59:33,470
Go in peace.

757
00:59:34,080 --> 00:59:35,080
All right.

758
00:59:36,580 --> 00:59:37,710
Take care.

759
00:59:40,150 --> 00:59:41,150
Yes.

760
01:00:13,580 --> 01:00:15,580
Doggy, come here!

761
01:00:32,570 --> 01:00:35,340
He passed on peacefully.

762
01:00:36,600 --> 01:00:37,610
Are you okay?

763
01:00:38,840 --> 01:00:40,640
You must have grown pretty attached to him.

764
01:00:41,480 --> 01:00:45,580
He really loved his wife so, so much.

765
01:00:47,450 --> 01:00:51,290
But she went her whole life without ever knowing.

766
01:00:52,750 --> 01:00:54,190
That's what's so heartbreaking.

767
01:00:55,860 --> 01:00:56,960
Like I said.

768
01:00:57,690 --> 01:01:00,430
You'll regret not saying "Thank you," "I'm sorry,"

769
01:01:00,930 --> 01:01:02,430
or "I love you" when you can.

770
01:01:03,630 --> 01:01:05,730
Yi Rang, if you want no regrets,

771
01:01:06,100 --> 01:01:07,940
you have to show your feelings sometimes.

772
01:01:14,780 --> 01:01:15,780
What is it?

773
01:01:19,250 --> 01:01:21,650
I'm not going to have any regrets.

774
01:01:23,180 --> 01:01:26,190
I know. That's not who you are, Yi Rang.

775
01:01:26,690 --> 01:01:27,890
Because I'm going to say it right now.

776
01:01:30,430 --> 01:01:31,430
You are?

777
01:01:34,160 --> 01:01:37,170
I'm telling you right now.

778
01:01:38,700 --> 01:01:39,700
How I feel.

779
01:02:07,930 --> 01:02:09,200
Hey, Doggy!

780
01:02:10,770 --> 01:02:11,770
Doggy?

781
01:02:14,000 --> 01:02:15,040
Don't tell me...

782
01:02:17,170 --> 01:02:18,470
Come play with me.

783
01:02:20,910 --> 01:02:22,240
What's your name?

784
01:02:24,350 --> 01:02:26,280
You can't just stop talking and walk away.

785
01:02:27,150 --> 01:02:28,350
You can't leave me hanging like this.

786
01:02:29,250 --> 01:02:30,450
Fine, whatever. Go.

787
01:02:32,720 --> 01:02:34,020
So cute.

788
01:02:53,980 --> 01:02:58,979
(Phantom Lawyer)

789
01:02:58,980 --> 01:03:00,179
What's wrong, mister?

790
01:03:00,180 --> 01:03:02,819
It's hard having so many unanswered questions.

791
01:03:02,820 --> 01:03:03,820
Because I can't remember.

792
01:03:03,821 --> 01:03:05,290
We have a missing elementary school student.

793
01:03:05,350 --> 01:03:07,289
He's in first grade, and he was wearing yellow rain boots.

794
01:03:07,290 --> 01:03:09,319
It's a boy, and he's wearing yellow rain boots.

795
01:03:09,320 --> 01:03:11,729
So, are you going to find my mom and dad for me now?

796
01:03:11,730 --> 01:03:14,999
A golf ball. This could be a vital clue to the location of death.

797
01:03:15,000 --> 01:03:16,260
I know who the child is.

798
01:03:17,970 --> 01:03:21,070
Mister, it's dangerous! Get a hold of yourself!
